#compdef udacimak
# =============================================================================
# udacimak — udacimak's "Udacity Nanodegree and Course
#          Downloader" — a Node.js CLI that scrapes the
#          Udacity Classroom API + classroom HTML pages
#          to download paid-tier Nanodegree video lessons,
#          quizzes, project descriptions, and supplementary
#          materials, then RENDERS them into self-contained
#          HTML lesson archives suitable for offline study
#          after a learner's Udacity subscription expires.
#          Distinguishing from `youtube-dl` / `yt-dlp` (raw
#          YouTube video downloaders — Udacity lessons mix
#          YouTube videos with proprietary text/quiz HTML
#          + interactive widgets that ydl can't capture),
#          screen-recording approaches (manual + lossy +
#          no text content), and the official Udacity
#          download buttons (only some courses; no
#          nanodegree-level batch export) by:
#            - CHEERIO HTML PARSING — uses cheeriojs/
#              cheerio v1.0 (this is the headline CLI
#              library that CLOSES Axis 41 on the TS-Node
#              side at 1/1/1; see taxonomy notes below) to
#              parse the Udacity Classroom DOM extracting
#              lesson titles, quiz prompts, video URLs,
#              instructor commentary text, and the
#              hierarchical Nanodegree → Part → Module →
#              Lesson → Concept tree structure
#            - UDACITY-CLASSROOM-API CLIENT — wraps the
#              undocumented `classroom-content.udacity.com`
#              JSON API used by the Udacity web UI;
#              authenticates via the `_jwt` cookie token
#              that the user extracts from their browser
#              (`udacimak settoken <jwt>`)
#            - TWO-PHASE WORKFLOW — clean separation of
#              `download` (fetch raw JSON + asset URLs)
#              from `render` (compile JSON → self-
#              contained HTML lessons with embedded
#              videos).  Allows downloading once + re-
#              rendering with different options later
#            - YOUTUBE-DL PIPELINE INTEGRATION — `render`
#              shells out to youtube-dl for the actual
#              YouTube video fetches; supports `-d, --
#              delay-youtube <secs>` to throttle requests
#              + avoid YouTube rate-limiting, `-s, --
#              subtitles` to also download per-video
#              captions, and `-v, --verbose` to surface
#              youtube-dl's debug output for
#              troubleshooting
#            - QUIZ-ANSWER PRESERVATION — `--userquizanswer`
#              flag preserves the user's previously-
#              submitted Programming Question code answers
#              in the rendered HTML, useful for archiving
#              completed work
#            - BULK RENDER via `renderdir` — `udacimak
#              renderdir <path>` walks a whole directory
#              of pre-downloaded Nanodegree JSON files +
#              renders each one to HTML in a single pass;
#              avoids hand-iterating multiple `render`
#              invocations
#            - NANODEGREE INVENTORY — `udacimak listnd`
#              hits the Classroom API to enumerate every
#              Nanodegree the authenticated user is
#              currently enrolled in OR has graduated
#              from; emits the IDs that `download` takes
#              as positional arguments
#            - DUAL AUTH PATHS — `udacimak login`
#              performs an interactive Udacity OAuth
#              flow + stores the resulting JWT locally;
#              `udacimak settoken <jwt>` lets advanced
#              users paste in a token extracted from
#              their browser's DevTools (the JWT cookie
#              is named `_jwt` in the udacity.com
#              cookie jar)
#            - COMMANDER ARGPARSE — built on TJ
#              Holowaychuk's commander.js v2.18; one of
#              the most-widely-used Node CLI parsers
#            - GLOBAL CONFIGURATION via process.global
#              — `--delay-youtube`, `--verbose`, `--
#              subtitles`, `--userquizanswer` set
#              `global.*` variables that the render
#              pipeline reads; allows the YouTube
#              downloader stage to access flags without
#              prop-drilling through nested function
#              calls
#            - 1,461+ STARS ON udacimak/udacimak —
#              substantial community traction; the
#              dominant choice for Udacity content
#              archival within the OSS ecosystem
#          Used by: Udacity students wanting to preserve
#          their completed Nanodegree lessons after their
#          subscription expires for personal study
#          reference (within the bounds of Udacity's
#          terms of service), bandwidth-constrained
#          learners pre-fetching lessons for offline
#          review, and instructional designers studying
#          Udacity's lesson structure for comparison
#          with their own platforms.
#
# AUTHORIZATION NOTE: udacimak downloads content the
# user is already authorized to access via their paid
# Udacity subscription.  Re-distribution of downloaded
# content is governed by Udacity's terms of service;
# users should review those terms before sharing
# archived materials.
#
# Author:  udacimak (npmjs.com/package/udacimak;
#          "Udacity Nanodegree and Course Downloader
#          developer").  Note: maintainer prefers the
#          udacimak handle over personal attribution.
# Source:  https://github.com/udacimak/udacimak
#          https://github.com/udacimak/udacimak/blob/master/src/index.js
#          https://github.com/udacimak/udacimak/blob/master/src/commands/
# Manpage: No traditional manpage; `udacimak --help`
#          (or `udacimak <command> --help`) shows
#          commander's auto-generated help.  Full docs
#          in repo README.md.
# Library: cheerio ^1.0.0-rc.2 (cheeriojs/cheerio —
#          Felix Böhm's "Fast, flexible, & lean
#          implementation of core jQuery designed
#          specifically for the server").  This is the
#          headline dependency for this completion's
#          axis-41 closing role; see taxonomy notes
#          below.  Also commander ^2.18 (Axis 1
#          argparse — TJ Holowaychuk's stdlib-style
#          Node CLI parser).
# License: MIT
# Status:  1,461+ stars on udacimak/udacimak;
#          published on npm as `udacimak`; active
#          maintenance for current Udacity Classroom
#          API.
#
