#
# WHY cheerio IS A DISTINCTIVE AXIS-41 CLOSER:
#
#   cheeriojs/cheerio is the *dominant* Node.js HTML
#   parsing library by every metric (stars, downloads,
#   production usage).  Distinguishing characteristics
#   in the TS-Node ecosystem:
#     1. JQUERY API COMPATIBILITY — `$('selector')`,
#        `.each()`, `.attr()`, `.text()`, `.html()`,
#        `.find()`, `.parent()`, `.children()`,
#        `.siblings()` precisely mirror jQuery's API
#     2. PARSE5 BACKEND — uses Ivan Nikulin's parse5
#        library (the WHATWG-compliant HTML5 parser,
#        used internally by jsdom + Angular's
#        renderer) for spec-compliant parsing of
#        real-world malformed HTML
#     3. HTMLPARSER2 FAST PATH — `cheerio.load(html,
#        { xmlMode: false, _useHtmlParser2: true })`
#        switches to Felix Böhm's faster (but less
#        spec-compliant) htmlparser2 for performance-
#        critical workflows
#     4. CSS-SELECT ENGINE — uses fb55/css-select for
#        CSS selector matching; supports CSS4
#        selectors (`:has()`, `:is()`, `:where()`,
#        `:not()`, `:nth-of-type()`, `:lang()`,
#        case-insensitive attribute matching, etc.)
#     5. STREAMING + SYNCHRONOUS API — cheerio
#        operations are SYNCHRONOUS (unlike many Node
#        APIs); makes scraping code linear + easy to
#        reason about without await/then chains
#     6. ZERO BROWSER DEPENDENCY — does NOT require
#        jsdom + does NOT spin up a real DOM
#        environment; pure parse-tree manipulation;
#        100× faster than jsdom for read-only
#        scraping
#     7. ~29,000 STARS ON cheeriojs/cheerio — THE
#        most-starred HTML parsing library in any
#        language ecosystem covered by this taxonomy
#     8. UNIVERSAL PRODUCTION USAGE — used by Next.js
